item.description:
arXiv:2405.03087v1 Announce Type: new 
Abstract: For Borel subsets $\Theta\subset O(d)\times \mathbb{R}^d$ (the set of all rigid motions) and $E\subset \mathbb{R}^d$, we define \begin{align*}
  \Theta(E):=\bigcup_{(g,z)\in \Theta}(gE+z). \end{align*} In this paper, we investigate the Lebesgue measure and Hausdorff dimension of $\Theta(E)$ given the dimensions of the Borel sets $E$ and $\Theta$, when $\Theta$ has product form. We also study this question by replacing rigid motions with the class of dilations and translations; and similarity transformations. The dimensional thresholds are sharp. Our results are variants of some previously known results in the literature when $E$ is restricted to smooth objects such as spheres, $k$-planes, and surfaces.
